                                Regent University offers a BBA that consists of 120 total undergraduate credits &#8211; 33 in the business major, 12 in the concentration, and 6 toward major electives. Some classes include Business Statistics, Corporate Finance, Micro and Macroeconomics, Political Economy, Business Policy, Personnel Law, Marketing Research, Sales Management, e-Commerce, and more. All students must also complete a Senior Research Project in order to graduate. Further, Regent offers 5 concentrations to allow students to tailor course work: Accounting, Economics, General Management, Human Resource Management, and Marketing. The broad-based curriculum is designed to blend fundamental business theory and real-world concepts. Alumni have gone onto careers in management, banking, marketing, human resources and more. As a Christian university, religious values may be incorporated throughout the degree.
                            </p>
                            <li><a href="http://www.regent.edu/acad/undergrad/academics/degree/business/">Homepage</a></li>
                            <li>Tuition per credit is $395.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3> 20. California State University, Fullerton</h3>
                            <p>
                                <img src="../../wp-content/uploads/2016/01/cal_state_fullerton-e1453750742229.png" alt="cal_state_fullerton" width="125" height="44" class="alignright size-full wp-image-3336" /><br />
                                California State University, Fullerton offers a BBA that consists of 19 courses that can be completed in three years. Core classes include Concepts of Federal Income Tax Accounting, Advanced Business Communication, Business Modeling Using Spreadsheets, Managing Operations, The International Economy, Economic Research Methods, Principles of Information Systems, Stress Management, and more. Courses deliver in accelerated 8-week blocks, and students may further accelerate completion time by transferring up to 63 credits. As a cohort-based degree, students work in a highly collaborative, intimate learning environment. In particular, this degree is designed for working professionals and allows students maximum schedule flexibility. CSU Fullerton alumni have gone on to work in social work, politics, law, public administration, urban and environmental planning, public relations, personnel, criminal justice, counseling and other service professions.
                            </p>
