                            <li>Tuition per credit is $500.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3> 21. Bemidji State University </h3>
                            <p>
                                <img src="../../wp-content/uploads/2016/01/bemidji_state-e1453750793831.png" alt="bemidji_state" width="125" height="34" class="alignright size-full wp-image-3337" /><br />
                                Bemidji State University offers a BBA that consists of 120 total undergraduate credits &#8211; 62-65 in the major. Classes include Principles of Accounting, Operations Management, Marketing, Business Statistics, Management Information Systems, Markets and Resource Allocation, and more. In addition, students may choose to concentrate in Management, Finance, Entrepreneurship, and Marketing. As a 2+2 degree-completion program, all students must have either already completed an associate&#8217;s degree or other bachelor&#8217;s to be eligible for the program, unless a 4-year student also plans on working. This program stresses real-world, practical learning and combines both business theory and practice. Alumni have gone on to careers as Bank Officers, Advertising Executives, Credit Analysts, Finance Directors, and more. Other relevant degrees offered include bachelors degrees in Computer Information Systems and Marketing Communication. Minors are available in Business and Management Information Systems.
                            </p>
