                                The University of Maryland University College consists of 120 undergraduate credits &#8211; 36 in the major core, plus electives. Required classes include Principles of Accounting, Introduction to Statistics, Management and Organization Theory, Organizational Leadership, Marketing Principles, Human Resource Management, Strategic Management, and more. In addition, students may choose between a wide variety of minors to further tailor their degree, including: Accounting, Finance, Political Science, Health Services Management, Small Business and Entrepreneurship, and more. A curriculum built on business theory and real-world practice was developed by employers, industry experts, and scholars. Thanks to a generous transfer policy of up to 90 credits, students with previous academic experience, military training, and/or testing may significantly accelerate graduation time.
                            </p>
