                            <li>Tuition per credit is $499.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3> 22 (tied). Drexel University Online, LeBow </h3>
                            <p>
                                <img src="../../wp-content/uploads/2015/02/14.-Drexel.png" alt="14. Drexel" width="125" height="125" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1848" srcset="http://www.bestcollegereviews.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/14.-Drexel.png 125w, http://www.bestcollegereviews.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/14.-Drexel-80x80.png 80w" sizes="(max-width: 125px) 100vw, 125px" /><br />
                                Drexel University Online offers a BBA that consists of 181 total undergraduate credits &#8211; 64 in the major. Thanks to a generous transfer policy, Drexel allows students with previous academic experience to waive up to 90 quarter credits, significantly accelerating graduation time. Core courses include Financial Accounting Foundations, Business Law, Principles of Macroeconomics, Principles of Microeconomics, Strategy and Competitive Advantage, Operations Management, Organizational Behavior, Entrepreneurship, and Business Statistics, among others. As a highly interactive program, Drexel provides students with a broad-based education that emphasizes both business theory and real-world practice, including the quantitative decision-making and behavioral factors in the workplace. With an emphasis on schedule flexibility, Drexel is appropriate for full-time students and working professionals alike. Note also that this program requires a one-time, four-day residency and intensive course.
                            </p>
