                                Southern New Hampshire University offers a BBA that consists of 120 total undergraduate credits &#8211; 30 in the business core. Required classes include Financial and Managerial Accounting, Business Law, International Business, Business Systems Analysis and Design, Strategic Management and Policy, and more. In addition, to allow students to customize their curriculum, SNHU offers 4 concentrations in Healthcare Administration, HR Management, Organizational Leadership, and Small Business Management. All students have 24/7 access to course materials and maximum schedule flexibility; classes deliver in accelerated 9-week blocks. (To further accelerate graduation time, SNHU also offers a generous transfer policy of up to 90 credits.) SHNU graduates look forward to leveraging a large and helpful alumni network to find careers across a wide range of areas in entry- and mid-level management and supervisory positions.
                            </p>
                            <li><a href="http://online.drexel.edu/online-degrees/business-degrees/bs-ba/index.aspx">Homepage</a></li>
                            <li>Tuition per credit is $320.</li>
                            </ul>
