                                Penn State&#8217;s World Campus offers a BBA that consists of 120 undergraduate credits &#8211; 59 in the business major. Core classes include Contemporary Skills for Business Professionals, Preparation for Career Management, Strategic Business Planning, Corporation Finance, International Business Operations, Supply Chain Management, and more. Further, to allow students the ability to customize their curriculum, Penn State offers 5 concentrations: Accounting, Entrepreneurship, Financial Services, Management and Marketing, and a customized individual option. With a broad-based curriculum founded in business theory and real-world practice, Penn State students learn all the fundamentals necessary to begin a successful professional career. Alumni have gone on to careers such as business marketing managers, management accountants, and financial analysts. Related degrees available online include an associate&#8217;s in business, a BS in Finance, and an MBA.
                            </p>
